anva-rc.jpg", "og:site_name": "Salesforce", "og:url": "https://www.salesforce.com/resources/articles/canva-expanded-enterprise-footprint/", "og:type": "website", "og:locale": "en_us", "body_text": "\n                \n                    RESOURCE CENTER \n                \n                \n                \n                \n             \n              \n                BROWSE BY CATEGORY\n              \n               \n             \n                \n                    Canva expands its footprint with the help of Salesforce. \n                \n                \n                \n                \n             \n                \n                    Time to read: 5 minutes \n                \n                \n                \n                \n             Launched in 2013, Canva began as a design tool for consumers and grew into a visual collaboration platform where everyone from small and medium businesses (SMBs) to Fortune 500s can create their content at speed and scale. \u201cWhen I think back to the beginning, almost everything was being managed on spreadsheets, including pipeline, account assignments, and inbound leads,\u201d said Duncan McIntyre, Head of Sales, APAC, at Canva. \n                \n                    Since the company\u2019s public launch in 2013, more than 7 billion designs have been created \n                \n                \n                \n                \n             \n                \n                    85% of Fortune 500 companies use Canva \n                \n                \n                \n                \n             Canva has over 800,000 templates, 100 million design assets, and 65 million monthly active users. Canva quickly capitalized on overwhelming demand with a tailored Salesforce enterprise offering supported by a new sales team.\u00a0 Gear up for a new opportunity . Optimize sales end to end . Facilitate collaboration and future growth .\u00a0 \n                \n                    1. Gear up for a n